WEBVTT

00:01.568 --> 00:03.869
             [♪♪♪]

00:54.254 --> 00:55.853
               Hi, there,
                Jeannie.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.855
              I, uh, thought
          you were still asleep.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.257
          I was gonna leave
           a note for you.

01:00.094 --> 01:01.193
                Here.

01:03.764 --> 01:05.731
That'll explain
everything, okay?

01:15.643 --> 01:16.808
         "Dear Jeannie,

01:16.843 --> 01:18.677
I saw no reason to disturb you.
         I am going--"

01:18.712 --> 01:21.680
                 Going away
            on a business trip?!

01:21.715 --> 01:24.482
           "Be a good genie.
      We'll see you in 10 day--"

01:24.517 --> 01:25.650
              [SCREAMS]

01:27.053 --> 01:29.588
  Oh, master, you must not go
  on this journey without me.

01:29.623 --> 01:32.457
        You do not know
what trouble you will get into.

01:32.493 --> 01:34.125
          Oh, please,
  let me out of here, master.

01:34.160 --> 01:35.493
            Jeannie.

01:43.036 --> 01:45.270
         Now, come on.
       Come on, Jeannie.

01:45.305 --> 01:46.604
         Now, stop that.

01:46.639 --> 01:48.506
       Jeannie. Jeannie.

01:48.541 --> 01:49.640
         Jeannie. Jeannie.

01:49.676 --> 01:50.675
            [GRUNTS]

01:57.751 --> 01:58.983
            [SIGHS]

02:00.820 --> 02:02.687
     I think you're trying
     to tell me something.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.592
         And I think
      I'd better listen.

02:12.666 --> 02:13.799
                    Ooh!

02:13.834 --> 02:16.868
          You and I
   had better have a talk.

02:16.904 --> 02:19.304
  You are headed for disaster.

02:23.877 --> 02:26.144
             [♪♪♪]

03:20.167 --> 03:21.967
 You were leaving without me.

03:22.002 --> 03:24.970
I explained everything
     in my note.

03:25.005 --> 03:26.637
    I was on my way
         to a--

03:26.673 --> 03:27.638
       [GRUNTS]

03:27.674 --> 03:29.307
To a military mission.

03:29.343 --> 03:31.509
                  Where?

03:31.544 --> 03:32.710
      To a city
  called Hollywood,

03:32.745 --> 03:34.012
      in a place
  called California,

03:34.047 --> 03:35.480
     where they make
     moving pictures.

03:35.515 --> 03:37.048
       Why must you go?

03:37.083 --> 03:40.285
  Because NASA has assigned me
    as a technical director

03:40.320 --> 03:41.419
          for an astronaut movie

03:41.455 --> 03:43.888
            that Mammoth Studios
              is going to make.

03:43.923 --> 03:46.691
You mean astronauts are going
to be in these moving pictures?

03:46.726 --> 03:47.626
                 Mm-hm. Yeah.
                 That's right.

03:47.661 --> 03:49.093
             Well, actually,
         it stars Rita Mitchell.

03:49.129 --> 03:51.596
         Rita Mitchell
      has had six husbands

03:51.632 --> 03:53.698
         and is looking
        for her seventh.

03:53.734 --> 03:56.367
 Oh, you are going to need
all the help I can give you.

04:00.541 --> 04:03.441
                    Say, that's
                  a cute outfit.

04:03.476 --> 04:04.843
              Where do you think
                 you're going?

04:04.878 --> 04:06.411
I am going with thee.

04:06.446 --> 04:10.649
I have never seen pictures
that move or a Rita Mitchell.

04:10.684 --> 04:14.385
              Well, it's really
            nothing much to see.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.721
       Besides, you've got
your studying to do, young lady.

04:16.757 --> 04:18.023
           And that's important.

04:18.058 --> 04:19.991
              You got 2000 years
                to catch up on.

04:20.027 --> 04:21.860
           Uh, by the way,
    have you done your homework?

04:21.894 --> 04:24.262
But there are so many things
in your newspapers and books

04:24.297 --> 04:25.363
that I do not understand.

04:25.398 --> 04:26.364
           Well, just take, uh--

04:26.399 --> 04:28.299
            Take the red crayon,

04:28.335 --> 04:30.135
                    and circle
                  all the things

04:30.170 --> 04:32.637
         you don't understand,
       and I'll explain it all--

04:32.672 --> 04:34.773
              Explain everything
                   to you...

04:36.643 --> 04:38.710
    [SIGHS]

04:38.746 --> 04:41.146
   Why can I not make
red circles in Hollywood?

04:41.181 --> 04:42.547
                       [SIGHS]
        [DOORBELL RINGS]

04:49.055 --> 04:50.354
                Come on.

04:50.390 --> 04:52.457
             Yes?
       The car is here, captain.

04:52.492 --> 04:53.691
            Huh?
            Can I get your bags?

04:53.727 --> 04:55.827
         Uh, no, no,
I'll take care of my own bags.

04:55.862 --> 04:57.495
    And I'll see you
 in a moment, sergeant.

04:57.531 --> 04:58.930
                       Yes, sir.
           Thank you.

05:00.300 --> 05:01.800
          Now, Jeannie.
              Now--

05:01.835 --> 05:03.401
           Hey, hey, hey,
         I got a good idea.

05:03.437 --> 05:05.537
               A very,
           very good idea.

05:06.339 --> 05:08.239
                       Look,
                    I'm gonna--

05:08.274 --> 05:11.743
         I-I'm gonna put my name
            on this envelope.

05:11.778 --> 05:14.111
          And I'm gonna give you
                the address

05:14.147 --> 05:16.013
                of my hotel...

05:16.049 --> 05:20.318
                in Hollywood,
                 California,

05:20.353 --> 05:21.920
                and anything
           you don't understand,

05:21.955 --> 05:23.888
            you just mail to me,

05:23.924 --> 05:27.124
         and I'll explain to you
             by return mail.

05:27.160 --> 05:28.159
                      See?

05:29.128 --> 05:31.295
        As you wish,
          master.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.598
    I hope your journey
  gives you much pleasure.

05:33.633 --> 05:35.633
          There are no pleasures
             involved in this.

05:35.669 --> 05:39.170
   This is a military assignment
    direct from Washington D.C.

05:39.205 --> 05:40.271
                     Now, you be
                    a good girl.

05:40.306 --> 05:44.108
     Oh, I am going to be
      a very good girl.

05:55.956 --> 05:56.922
            Thank you,
             Jeannie.

05:56.957 --> 05:57.956
           Write often.

06:01.562 --> 06:03.361
             [♪♪♪]

06:35.028 --> 06:36.494
           Thank you.

06:40.333 --> 06:41.732
     Here you are.

06:41.768 --> 06:43.401
       Thanks.

06:43.436 --> 06:44.902
             Rita Mitchell, huh?
[KNOCK]

06:44.937 --> 06:46.003
Captain Nelson?
                       Mm-hm?

06:46.039 --> 06:48.339
A letter for you, sir.
                 Oh, thanks.

06:48.375 --> 06:52.910
      Rita, or should I say,
          Ms. Mitchell,

06:52.945 --> 06:55.146
     as your technical advisor,

06:55.182 --> 06:56.147
   I want you to know

06:56.183 --> 06:58.650
  that no sacrifice
    is too great.

06:59.786 --> 07:02.387
                    Master,
               what is Medicare?

07:02.422 --> 07:04.522
        Jeannie,
what are you doing here?

07:04.558 --> 07:06.357
Don't tell. Don't tell me.
     I know. I know.

07:06.393 --> 07:07.758
   You couldn't finish
       the article

07:07.794 --> 07:09.360
    until you knew
 what a "Medicare" was.

07:09.396 --> 07:10.461
             Thou art so clever.

07:10.497 --> 07:11.529
     [CHUCKLES]

07:11.565 --> 07:12.697
        Oh, God,

07:12.732 --> 07:14.232
             if there's anything
                I can't stand,

07:14.267 --> 07:15.900
       it's a smart-aleck genie.

07:15.935 --> 07:17.235
             If I was so clever,

07:17.270 --> 07:19.304
         I'd never have opened
      your bottle on that beach.

07:19.339 --> 07:21.972
   Oh, art thou
   really sorry?

07:22.008 --> 07:23.708
                     No,
                 I guess not.

07:23.743 --> 07:25.710
          I've grown accustomed
              to your smoke.

07:25.745 --> 07:26.878
       Oh,

07:26.914 --> 07:28.847
                    so that
               is Rita Mitchell?

07:28.882 --> 07:30.949
               She is beautiful.

07:30.984 --> 07:34.051
  "Rita Mitchell's six husbands.
    Who will be number seven?"

07:34.087 --> 07:36.153
         [PHONE RINGS]

07:36.189 --> 07:37.188
                    Yes?

07:38.558 --> 07:40.891
                Yes, this is
            Captain Nelson here.

07:40.927 --> 07:44.128
                Oh, h-hello,
                 Mr. Tracy.

07:44.163 --> 07:45.129
                   Uh-huh.

07:45.164 --> 07:46.731
              St-stage 12-A?

07:46.766 --> 07:48.466
                Right, I--
         I can leave right away.

07:48.501 --> 07:49.767
                   Right.
                 Thank you.

07:49.802 --> 07:50.868
            That's the producer.

07:50.903 --> 07:52.337
           He's waiting for me
             at the studio.

07:52.372 --> 07:53.504
           What am I gonna do
               with you?

07:53.540 --> 07:55.740
 Take me with you.
        As what? A harem dancer?

07:55.775 --> 07:57.074
This is business.

07:57.910 --> 08:00.778
                     Meet
              thy new secretary.

08:00.813 --> 08:02.447
Jeannie, I'm going to put
my foot down.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.014
You are not gonna
leave this room.

08:04.050 --> 08:05.783
I can't have you--
            We are late, master.

08:11.758 --> 08:13.558
                Pardon me,
         um, I'm Captain Nelson.

08:13.593 --> 08:15.460
           I have an appointment
              with Mr. Tracy.

08:15.495 --> 08:16.627
Oh, yes, captain.

08:16.663 --> 08:19.264
Mr. Tracy is waiting
for you on stage 12-A.

08:19.299 --> 08:21.499
You'll find it down this way.
To the left.

08:21.534 --> 08:22.867
                      Thank you.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.975
                Charlie,

08:30.010 --> 08:32.043
I want you to make
Rita Mitchell's spacesuit

08:32.078 --> 08:33.477
look like a bikini.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.179
Remember, the male eyes
of America

08:35.215 --> 08:36.914
expect to see her that way.

08:38.784 --> 08:41.885
                     Well,
                Captain Nelson.

08:41.921 --> 08:44.222
        I see it didn't take you
            long to get here.

08:44.256 --> 08:49.294
        I-- I-- I can't tell you
       how glad I am to see you.

08:49.329 --> 08:50.461
TONY:
Thank you very much.

08:50.496 --> 08:53.865
     This is my secretary,
        Miss...Jeannie.

08:53.900 --> 08:55.934
    And what is your first name,
              my dear?

08:55.969 --> 08:57.168
   Uh, Jeannie.

08:57.203 --> 08:59.403
                     Oh,
               Jeannie Jeannie.

08:59.439 --> 09:01.138
     We haven't had one of those
             around here

09:01.174 --> 09:02.774
             since Simone Simon.

09:04.010 --> 09:07.879
        N-now our picture deals
      with an American astronaut

09:07.914 --> 09:09.481
                 named Thompson,

09:09.516 --> 09:13.050
   who finds himself in a rather
      interesting predicament,

09:13.086 --> 09:16.053
       inasmuch as it has become
        necessary to reduce him

09:16.089 --> 09:17.489
       to the size of a pinhead.

09:17.524 --> 09:18.723
The size of a pinhead?

09:18.758 --> 09:21.226
         You see, captain,

09:21.261 --> 09:25.563
          by reducing
    this little astronaut...

09:27.868 --> 09:30.701
     ...it is now possible
         to inject him

09:30.737 --> 09:34.639
         into the body
    of a Russian astronaut.

09:36.543 --> 09:38.076
              Say,
     about the size of you.

09:39.779 --> 09:43.548
           Now, here,
     we have an enlargement

09:43.583 --> 09:44.816
       of the astronaut.

09:44.851 --> 09:46.751
                          Oh,
                      he's cute.

09:46.786 --> 09:50.421
            Once inside
       the Russian astronaut,

09:50.457 --> 09:57.962
     the tiny American works
 his way slowly but torturously

09:57.997 --> 10:05.503
        through bone and marrow
          into his very brain.

10:05.539 --> 10:08.039
                    Oh, even I
                 cannot do that.

10:11.311 --> 10:13.978
          I'll bet you could.

10:14.013 --> 10:15.646
     She's got a sense of humor,
                 huh?

10:15.682 --> 10:18.450
Oh, yes-- Yes, she's
a million laughs.

10:18.485 --> 10:19.684
What does he do--

10:19.719 --> 10:20.685
The little astronaut.

10:20.720 --> 10:21.953
  --once he gets
  inside there?

10:21.988 --> 10:23.721
      I hope he does not sneeze.

10:23.757 --> 10:25.223
          Not a bad idea.

10:27.026 --> 10:29.560
         On second thought,
             negative.

10:29.595 --> 10:32.964
It might scatter the information
         he's obtained.

10:33.499 --> 10:34.465
             Now--

10:34.500 --> 10:38.269
           Now we have
       the little astronaut

10:38.304 --> 10:41.538
    inside the big astronaut,

10:41.574 --> 10:45.743
 and he has obtained information
       vital and necessary

10:45.779 --> 10:48.079
 to the defense of our country.

10:50.549 --> 10:51.582
         Any questions?

10:51.617 --> 10:52.583
       Yes.

10:52.618 --> 10:54.719
How does the little
astronaut get out?

10:54.755 --> 10:55.954
         Good question.

11:00.227 --> 11:02.961
      How does he get out?

11:04.798 --> 11:07.632
     I'd better track down
      that writer of ours,

11:07.667 --> 11:10.135
        wherever he is.

11:10.170 --> 11:12.203
       I want you to know
        that we have put

11:12.239 --> 11:15.907
      the best story minds
     in Hollywood on this.

11:15.942 --> 11:19.644
 And we have spared no expense
          in casting.

11:19.679 --> 11:21.479
      We've done our part.

11:21.514 --> 11:23.347
   Now you must do your part.

11:23.382 --> 11:25.082
  And what's that,
        sir?

11:25.118 --> 11:27.652
 Keep this picture believable.

11:29.689 --> 11:31.789
              MAN:
         Ms. Mitchell,
   ready on the set, please.

11:31.825 --> 11:35.693
   I want you to meet our lovely
   astronaut, Ms. Rita Mitchell.

11:41.668 --> 11:42.867
Ready,
Ms. Mitchell.

11:44.904 --> 11:49.340
  Rita, darling, I want you
to meet our technical advisor,

11:49.375 --> 11:51.943
         the famous
   Captain Tony Thompson.

11:51.978 --> 11:52.944
                       Nelson.

11:52.979 --> 11:54.045
       Oh, well,
     I'm impressed.

11:54.080 --> 11:55.346
         Henry,
    I never thought

11:55.381 --> 11:58.650
   I'd get to meet
a real-life astronaut.

11:58.685 --> 12:01.552
    We-- Well, I never thought
  I'd get to meet a real-life...

12:01.587 --> 12:02.887
                  Rita Mitchell.

12:02.922 --> 12:06.591
I'm giving a little cocktail
party tonight in your honor

12:06.626 --> 12:08.459
at my house.

12:08.494 --> 12:10.795
   Um, shall we say
         7:00?

12:10.830 --> 12:12.530
        Oh,
 7:00 will be fine.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.065
         Good.

12:16.336 --> 12:19.137
O-oh, and of course,
you're invited too.

12:19.172 --> 12:20.538
Oh, thank you.

12:20.573 --> 12:21.839
It will be a welcome change

12:21.874 --> 12:24.208
from staying home alone
with my bottle.

12:24.844 --> 12:25.977
                      [COUGHS]

12:26.012 --> 12:27.711
     They're ready for you,
         Ms. Mitchell.

12:27.747 --> 12:28.813
     Oh, yes.

12:30.317 --> 12:32.617
             [♪♪♪]

12:38.157 --> 12:41.492
Oh, there you are, darling.
          Come in.

12:41.528 --> 12:42.627
              I am sorry
             we are late,

12:42.662 --> 12:45.430
        but Captain Nelson
    had much dictating to do.

12:45.465 --> 12:47.765
Oh, well, we're going to make
him forget all of that.

12:47.800 --> 12:49.900
         I'm three olives
          ahead of you.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.035
         [BOTH CHUCKLE]

12:51.070 --> 12:53.338
       This is Captain Nelson's
              secretary.

12:53.373 --> 12:55.206
           And I think maybe
      I'm in the wrong business.

12:55.242 --> 12:56.374
                        [LAUGHS]

12:56.409 --> 12:58.576
            Maybe <i> you're</i>
        in the wrong business.

12:58.612 --> 13:00.378
       Isn't she scrumptious?

13:00.413 --> 13:01.879
        This is Jeannie Jeannie.

13:01.914 --> 13:03.047
         A name worth repeating.

13:03.082 --> 13:05.316
             This is Hubie,
        and this is Chris Daily.

13:05.352 --> 13:06.917
     How do you do?

13:06.953 --> 13:10.587
TRACY:
Tell me, how long
have you been a secretary?

13:10.623 --> 13:13.057
                Uh,
            since noon.

13:13.092 --> 13:14.458
                          Oh?

13:14.493 --> 13:17.861
         And where did you study
               stenography?

13:17.897 --> 13:20.464
      Uh, where did I study,
            uh, what?

13:22.868 --> 13:25.102
I've always been
fascinated by space.

13:25.138 --> 13:27.038
I'm a scientist at heart.
                 [CHUCKLES]

13:27.073 --> 13:28.605
             No kidding?
       You don't look like one.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.673
    Don't laugh.

13:29.708 --> 13:31.809
I have a master's degree
      in physics.

13:31.844 --> 13:33.010
                  Really?

13:33.046 --> 13:34.812
           Well, maybe you're
         in the wrong business.

13:34.847 --> 13:37.247
         Maybe you should think
       of becoming an astronaut.

13:38.384 --> 13:39.817
                      Jeannie.

13:39.852 --> 13:44.021
    You don't mind if I call you
          Jeannie, do you?

13:44.057 --> 13:45.522
You know,
you really ought to think

13:45.558 --> 13:48.592
about becoming a movie star
like Rita Mitchell.

13:48.628 --> 13:51.829
 There aren't many girls
     like you around.

13:51.864 --> 13:53.231
               How did you know?

13:53.266 --> 13:54.865
    Well, I--

13:54.901 --> 13:55.900
    [CHUCKLES]

13:55.936 --> 13:57.568
               You know, honey,

13:57.603 --> 14:00.004
       you're my kind of people.

14:00.040 --> 14:01.472
                 [CHUCKLES]

14:02.675 --> 14:05.343
           The, uh, neck ring
        fits onto the suit here,

14:05.378 --> 14:07.178
               and the helmet
              threads onto it.

14:09.882 --> 14:12.550
                 And the unit is
                carried by hand.

14:12.585 --> 14:14.686
         Do you believe in fate?

14:14.721 --> 14:16.487
      Oh, yes.

14:16.523 --> 14:17.721
                I do too.

14:17.756 --> 14:18.822
      Oh,

14:18.858 --> 14:19.890
you and I are gonna make

14:19.925 --> 14:22.693
beautiful musicals together.

14:22.728 --> 14:24.495
            Let's have a drink
                 on that.

14:27.399 --> 14:29.033
Well, I can't offer you
the excitement

14:29.068 --> 14:31.168
I'm sure you're used to
as an astronaut,

14:31.203 --> 14:34.805
but I do hope you'll let me
show you the real Hollywood.

14:34.841 --> 14:35.806
       [THUNDER CRASHES]

14:35.842 --> 14:37.041
           That sounds exciting.

14:37.076 --> 14:39.576
Good, then we'll start
 with lunch tomorrow

14:39.612 --> 14:40.577
  in Beverly Hills.

14:40.613 --> 14:41.779
                Beverly Hills.
                 About 1:00?

14:41.814 --> 14:43.614
            Oh!

14:43.650 --> 14:45.482
    Oh!
                Oh, boy!

14:45.518 --> 14:48.318
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

14:50.489 --> 14:52.690
                    Jeannie,
               you cut this out!

14:52.725 --> 14:54.058
           Now, Jeannie,
          I'm not kidding,

14:54.093 --> 14:55.359
           this time
      you've gone too far!

14:55.394 --> 14:56.393
              Now,
       just knock it off!

15:03.302 --> 15:04.835
       [WITH STUFFY NOSE]
       You rained on me.

15:04.871 --> 15:06.837
        Go on, deny it.

15:06.873 --> 15:08.773
Deny that you were
 that rainstorm.

15:09.542 --> 15:10.808
              I refuse to answer

15:10.843 --> 15:12.977
             on the grounds
       that you might get angry.

15:13.012 --> 15:15.746
        Get angry?
I'd like to mail you home.

15:15.782 --> 15:17.181
  Your home, not mine.

15:18.617 --> 15:21.018
    You are going out again
with the woman of many husbands?

15:21.054 --> 15:22.687
   Yes, as a matter
    of fact, I am.

15:22.722 --> 15:24.855
 We're gonna have lunch
and discuss the picture.

15:24.891 --> 15:26.924
And I don't want you
raining in my soup.

15:28.895 --> 15:30.494
                  Master,

15:30.529 --> 15:33.097
      if I were a movie star,
   would you have lunch with me?

15:33.132 --> 15:34.264
       Sure. Sure.
        Any time.

15:34.300 --> 15:35.633
  I'll see you later.
       Goodbye.

15:37.103 --> 15:40.171
   Then I will have to become
         a movie star.

15:40.206 --> 15:42.106
      I do not know how,
   but if it will save him,

15:42.142 --> 15:43.341
      then I must do it.

15:44.210 --> 15:46.144
             [♪♪♪]

16:06.232 --> 16:08.199
    May I get down now, please?

16:10.169 --> 16:11.302
                       Hold it.
                     Don't move.

16:11.337 --> 16:12.670
              You could get hurt
                   up there.

16:12.705 --> 16:13.838
              I'll let you down.

16:15.875 --> 16:16.874
                 Ooh.

16:21.614 --> 16:23.380
    I wish you extras would quit
           playing around

16:23.415 --> 16:24.648
             with our equipment.

16:24.683 --> 16:26.617
Hey, who are you?
You're not one of our extras.

16:26.652 --> 16:28.385
         I am looking
        for Mr. Tracy.

16:28.420 --> 16:29.920
               Uh,
           is he here?

16:29.955 --> 16:32.557
Oh, is he
expecting you?

16:32.592 --> 16:34.826
             Oh, no,
       I do not think so.

16:34.861 --> 16:37.528
But last night he said I should
 be a star like Rita Mitchell.

16:37.563 --> 16:38.529
         Oh.

16:38.564 --> 16:41.199
                   Oh-ho,
            just like that, huh?

16:41.234 --> 16:42.533
              Yes.

16:42.569 --> 16:44.035
   I would like to be a star
          by tonight,

16:44.070 --> 16:45.570
 if it is not too much trouble
            for you.

16:45.605 --> 16:48.739
Oh, no, no. No trouble
at all, ha-ha-ha.

16:48.774 --> 16:50.574
You know what she needs?

16:50.609 --> 16:51.876
  A screen test.

16:51.911 --> 16:54.444
      One screen test
      coming right up.

16:58.084 --> 16:59.050
                What can you do?

16:59.085 --> 17:00.684
              Do?

17:02.255 --> 17:03.254
       I can disappear.

17:04.290 --> 17:05.556
         She can disappear.

17:05.590 --> 17:06.589
[CHUCKLES]

17:07.560 --> 17:08.858
           But not before
          I get your name

17:08.894 --> 17:10.127
        and phone number,
             sweetie.

17:12.765 --> 17:15.066
    Well, I can make myself
          into smoke.

17:15.101 --> 17:17.367
            Oh, no, no.
        Everybody does that.

17:18.171 --> 17:19.270
  Did you have a scene ready?

17:19.805 --> 17:20.771
           A scene?

17:20.806 --> 17:22.806
                 A scene. Lines.

17:22.842 --> 17:24.075
           Some dialogue.

17:24.109 --> 17:27.010
Do you know, uh,
"The Face on the Barroom Floor"?

17:27.714 --> 17:29.847
               No.

17:29.882 --> 17:32.950
        But I can recite
 <i> The Rubáiyát of Omar Khayyám.</i>

17:32.985 --> 17:34.952
       He would not mind.
    He was a friend of mine.

17:37.423 --> 17:38.556
          A friend of yours,
                 huh?

17:38.591 --> 17:40.391
                    Oh, yes.

17:40.426 --> 17:42.893
            He used to try out
         all his material on me.

17:44.697 --> 17:45.996
          He wrote poetry.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.334
            Oh, look.

17:50.370 --> 17:54.204
       Oh, how lovely.
     It's just like home.

17:55.307 --> 17:56.273
            It is empty.

17:56.308 --> 17:57.508
           [LAUGHS]

17:59.579 --> 18:01.412
      Isn't she beautiful.

18:01.447 --> 18:02.946
            Isn't she beautiful.

18:02.982 --> 18:04.248
         Say, listen.

18:04.283 --> 18:06.350
Why don't you recite
some of your friend's poetry

18:06.386 --> 18:07.551
 for the test?

18:07.587 --> 18:09.152
    I-if you so desire.

18:16.061 --> 18:17.060
   Action.

18:18.698 --> 18:19.730
              [GONG]

18:24.203 --> 18:29.874
   <i> The Moving Finger writes</i>
  <i> And, having writ, moves on</i>

18:29.909 --> 18:32.676
   <i> Nor all thy piety nor wit</i>

18:32.712 --> 18:36.113
       <i> Can lure it back</i>
     <i> To cancel half a line</i>

18:36.148 --> 18:39.417
  <i> Nor all thy tears wash out</i>
         <i> A word of it</i>

18:39.452 --> 18:44.021
       <i> And when like her</i>
    <i> O Sákí, you shall pass</i>

18:44.056 --> 18:48.358
       <i> Among the guests</i>
  <i> Star-scattered in the grass</i>

18:48.394 --> 18:50.961
<i> And in your joyous errand</i>
     <i> Reach the spot</i>

18:50.996 --> 18:53.363
<i> Where I made one</i>

18:53.399 --> 18:56.199
   <i> Turn down an empty glass</i>

18:57.836 --> 19:00.837
           [APPLAUSE]

19:00.873 --> 19:02.773
   Who is she?
         I'm sorry, Mr. Huberts.

19:02.808 --> 19:04.441
             I didn't know you
           came back from lunch.

19:04.477 --> 19:05.743
             I'll get rid of her
                 right away.

19:05.778 --> 19:06.777
Get rid of her?

19:10.783 --> 19:12.082
I wanna test her.

19:12.117 --> 19:13.083
                      Oh.

19:13.118 --> 19:14.418
       Screen test?

19:14.453 --> 19:16.086
        Jeannie,
they were putting you on.

19:16.121 --> 19:18.054
Putting me on what?

19:18.090 --> 19:19.356
        I mean,
 they were teasing you.

19:19.392 --> 19:20.957
      You just can't
 walk into a film studio

19:20.993 --> 19:22.025
 and get a screen test.

19:22.060 --> 19:23.694
       I did it for you.

19:23.729 --> 19:25.796
      Now I can please you
 as much as Rita Mitchell does

19:25.831 --> 19:27.665
    because I'm going to be
          a big star.

19:27.700 --> 19:29.032
         Yeah,
      who said so?

19:29.067 --> 19:31.034
         Jason Huberts.

19:31.069 --> 19:32.569
     He is a very nice man.

19:32.605 --> 19:34.104
    He is going to help me.

19:34.139 --> 19:35.706
             He's gonna help you
                    what?

19:36.309 --> 19:38.609
          Oh, master.

19:38.644 --> 19:40.578
   Is it that you are jealous
            of him?

19:40.613 --> 19:41.679
                     No,
            don't be ridiculous.

19:41.714 --> 19:43.080
                Of course
         I'm not jealous of him.

19:43.115 --> 19:45.082
    I just-- Well, I hate to see
        a nice genie like you

19:45.117 --> 19:46.083
        make a fool of yourself.

19:46.118 --> 19:47.084
                     That's all.

19:47.119 --> 19:49.019
           He makes
    a very handsome caliph.

19:49.054 --> 19:51.389
      Listen, the last time
 you got involved with a caliph,

19:51.424 --> 19:53.724
          it cost you the best
        2000 years of your life.

19:53.760 --> 19:56.560
I wish you would not speak to me
as though I were a child.

19:56.596 --> 19:58.996
After all, I'm--
I'm older than you are.

19:59.031 --> 20:00.898
                  Yeah,
         on a mere technicality.

20:00.933 --> 20:02.866
       Jeannie, I'm just telling
          these things to you

20:02.902 --> 20:04.502
              for your own good.

20:04.537 --> 20:06.737
            Just stay away
     from that movie crowd, huh?

20:06.773 --> 20:08.439
               I've gotta go
          and meet Ms. Mitchell.

20:08.474 --> 20:11.141
Oh, I was hoping that you would
    come see my screen test.

20:11.176 --> 20:13.377
        Well, I can't.
 The whole thing's ridiculous.

20:13.412 --> 20:14.378
      Where is it showing?

20:14.413 --> 20:15.612
         At the studio.

20:15.648 --> 20:17.615
         In Mr. Tracy's
        projection room.

20:18.618 --> 20:20.050
             Well,
   I have another engagement.

20:20.085 --> 20:21.084
                I can't.

20:28.027 --> 20:29.794
This had better be good,
         Hubie.

20:29.829 --> 20:33.664
You're taking me away from--
Oh, hello, Jeannie.

20:33.700 --> 20:35.132
   You're gonna love this kid,
              Henry.

20:35.167 --> 20:36.634
  I can't wait.

20:36.669 --> 20:38.636
    All right,
     roll it.

20:38.671 --> 20:41.772
      [PROJECTOR WHIRRING]

20:43.275 --> 20:44.542
              MAN:
            <i> Action.</i>

20:57.990 --> 21:00.123
<i> The rose is pale and lifeless</i>

21:00.159 --> 21:02.560
<i> compared to thy ruby lips.</i>

21:02.595 --> 21:04.595
                   JEANNIE:
             <i> Oh, mighty caliph,</i>

21:04.630 --> 21:07.031
    <i> thine arms have such might,</i>
        <i> they leave me weak.</i>

21:08.400 --> 21:10.634
<i> The strength cometh</i>
   <i> from my love.</i>

21:10.670 --> 21:11.669
                     <i> Hold me.</i>

21:12.939 --> 21:15.539
         What is this?
        What's the gag?

21:17.377 --> 21:19.076
HUBERTS:
<i> My desert siren,</i>

21:19.111 --> 21:21.779
<i> When thou lookest at me</i>
<i> this way,</i>

21:21.814 --> 21:25.215
<i> it seemeth as though thou wert</i>
<i> looking right through me.</i>

21:29.956 --> 21:31.422
All right, cut it.
Cut it.

21:32.425 --> 21:33.790
     Who's the droll fellow

21:33.825 --> 21:36.726
 that thought this little stunt
       would be amusing?

21:36.762 --> 21:37.861
                You,
               Hubie?

21:37.896 --> 21:39.930
            Me?

21:39.965 --> 21:41.331
          I tell you,
     she was in that test.

21:41.367 --> 21:42.533
      She was brilliant.

21:42.568 --> 21:45.536
It must have been the cameraman
or special effects.

21:47.273 --> 21:50.874
  Dragging a busy man away
    for this nonsense...

21:50.909 --> 21:53.611
when he's got little astronauts
        to worry about.

21:55.348 --> 21:56.347
Jeannie, I--

21:58.718 --> 22:02.453
I don't know what happened,
but I'm terribly sorry.

22:30.749 --> 22:32.483
  [SNEEZES]

22:33.152 --> 22:34.818
    Sorry.

22:36.255 --> 22:38.489
                [SOBBING]
             Master, wha--?
        What are you doing here?

22:40.359 --> 22:42.058
I came to see
your screen test.

22:45.030 --> 22:47.764
 I did not know they could not
      make pictures of me.

22:49.936 --> 22:51.769
   Jeannie.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.337
       Here.

22:53.372 --> 22:55.973
If there's anything I can't
stand, it's a crying genie.

23:00.179 --> 23:01.779
             You are being kind.

23:03.048 --> 23:04.482
                   Do--
          Do not bother with me.

23:04.517 --> 23:06.350
               You will be late
              for Rita Mitchell.

23:07.687 --> 23:09.854
I canceled that date.

23:09.889 --> 23:12.823
     I promise I-I will not rain
           on you anymore.

23:16.963 --> 23:18.796
                     You what?

23:18.831 --> 23:20.498
I canceled that date.

23:21.934 --> 23:23.066
                          Why?

23:24.069 --> 23:26.604
        Well, I was
a little worried about you.

23:28.975 --> 23:32.109
                     Oh, master.

23:32.144 --> 23:34.778
            I cannot believe it.

23:34.814 --> 23:36.981
You can't believe what?

23:37.016 --> 23:38.081
          I have taken thee away

23:38.117 --> 23:40.851
     from the biggest movie star
            in Hollywood.

23:40.886 --> 23:42.419
                [LAUGHING]

23:43.322 --> 23:45.689
     Well,
that's show biz.

23:51.330 --> 23:53.196
             [♪♪♪]

24:00.406 --> 24:01.872
               Master,
          what is all this?

24:01.908 --> 24:05.209
Hm? Oh, these are footprints
of Hollywood movie stars.

24:05.244 --> 24:06.210
Oh.

24:06.245 --> 24:08.212
        There's Clark Gable,
    Wallace Beery, Eddie Cantor.

24:08.247 --> 24:09.280
Master.
         Hm?

24:09.315 --> 24:11.681
              Our visit here
          was unforgettable too.

24:11.717 --> 24:13.083
 Yes, it was.

24:13.119 --> 24:16.387
    Then why do we not put our
  footprints in the cement, huh?

24:16.422 --> 24:18.355
Well, for one thing,
you can't do it that way.

24:18.391 --> 24:21.091
    Uh, the cement
would have to be soft.

24:50.022 --> 24:53.690
             [♪♪♪]
